provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:31:This workspace is building a domain-general design methodology in which diverse perspectives deliberate, produce durable specifications, and preserve the reasoning behind decisions (provenance) so that future readers — human or agent — can reconstruct not just what was decided but what was considered and why. The methodology is self-hosting: it evolves by applying its own process to itself.
provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:76:**Q2. Placement.** Where does the field live in a session's provenance?
provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:80:- Option C: a new per-session manifest file (e.g., `decisions.manifest.yaml`) under the provenance directory.
provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:93:Specify: which retroactivity policy is right, what marks the boundary (date, session number, artefact-presence heuristic), what `validate.sh` does when it encounters a pre-adoption decision record, and whether backfilling counts as editing immutable provenance (Session 004 D-017 and workspace-structure §provenance/ mandate immutability; a retroactive addition arguably violates that mandate — or arguably is a schema migration that accompanies the rule's introduction).
provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:150:| 10 | No uncommitted changes to provenance files (heuristic) | Warning | unconditional |
provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:165:Decision records live in `02-decisions.md` within each session's provenance directory. Each decision is a Markdown section of this form:
provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:251:Return your response as stdout. It will be committed verbatim (including any banner your runtime emits) as `provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md`. Do not edit it post-submission. Do not coordinate with Claude perspectives.
provenance/006-triggers-met-schema/01d-perspective-outsider.md:299:I reject full backfill. The immutability rule is load-bearing, and backfilling `triggers_met` into D-001 through D-036 would not be a neutral formatting migration. It would be a present-day reinterpretation of old decisions, recorded as if it had been contemporaneous metadata. That is exactly the sort of silent provenance rewrite the methodology says not to do.
