provenance/012-methodology-naming/01c-perspective-skeptic.md:22:2. **62 decisions with provenance.** Accumulation, not maturation. Decision count scales with session count mechanically — it measures throughput, not convergence. How many of D-001 through D-062 have been tested against actual revision pressure from external use? The honest answer is: very few. Most were stress-tested only by subsequent internal work, which is the same workspace reasoning with itself.
provenance/012-methodology-naming/01c-perspective-skeptic.md:49:- Hides: provenance, preservation of dissent, self-hosting.
provenance/012-methodology-naming/01c-perspective-skeptic.md:55:- Hides: the nine-activity operational frame; external artefact output. A reader hearing "Provenance" would expect a system for tracking data/model lineage — which is exactly what the word denotes in computing and archival practice. [external analogue: W3C PROV, data-provenance literature] — severe collision.
provenance/012-methodology-naming/01c-perspective-skeptic.md:146:4. **Preservation-of-dissent integrity.** Session 001's dissent is in the record. Overruling it when no new evidence has arrived (only more sessions of the same workspace) is bad provenance. The methodology would be breaking its own rule.
provenance/012-methodology-naming/01c-perspective-skeptic.md:187:1. **Treating a future kernel revision as disclosure-of-error rather than identity-update.** Right now, if Session 020 revises the kernel to eight activities or ten, that revision is a specification change and its provenance sits in a decision. Once named — especially if the name emphasises the nine-activity structure — the same revision becomes an "identity update." The provenance load grows. The revision becomes harder to execute honestly.
provenance/012-methodology-naming/01c-perspective-skeptic.md:191:**Suppose, against my Q1/Q5 answer, a name is chosen.** Take the least-bad candidate (I will not endorse one; I will describe effects hypothetically). Any name with operational flavour (kernel-ish, activity-ish) would steer future sessions toward further operational-kernel refinement and away from the methodology's other equally real features (provenance, preservation-of-dissent). Any name with provenance flavour would do the opposite. There is no neutral name. The claim that a "neutral-sounding" name defers the question is, on examination, the claim that the methodology should adopt a name that pretends not to steer. That is worse than steering openly, because it hides the steering.
provenance/046-session/00-assessment.md:3:title: Path OS — First external-application bootstrap (disaster-response scenario workspace at /Users/ericmccowan/Development/selvedge-disaster-response/); single-orchestrator Case Steward infrastructure build; tools/bootstrap-external-workspace.sh produced; engine-feedback outbox exercised by this run's setup; engine-v7 preserved (preservation window count 10 new longest extended); auto-memory disabled for this workspace per operator directive (all provenance in-workspace going forward)
provenance/046-session/00-assessment.md:37:8. Operator-flagged risk: **tangling scenario-specific artefacts with self-development provenance**. Operator offered fork: first run of an external application, with scripts to bootstrap a new workspace based on the specs and instructions on how feedback is delivered.
