specifications/reference-validation-v1.md:28:**C1 — Documented solution with auditable provenance.** The reference must be a solution whose origin can be pointed at: identifiable author, team, or institution; dated publication or delivery; accessible URL or citation. The reference must have been published or archived at least 12 months before the exercise-opening session. A snapshot of the reference URL or document is committed into the exercise's provenance directory as an anti-drift witness at Cell 1 open.
specifications/reference-validation-v1.md:45:- **Uncertainty-declared:** the provenance write-up for the reference must include the author's own account of what they are uncertain about in their solution — which parts they might have done differently, what they would change with hindsight. This provides a tolerance band for divergence scoring: divergence within author-flagged uncertainty bands is scored as legitimate design judgment, not as substantive divergence.
specifications/reference-validation-v1.md:101:**Outputs.** Sealed case pack (reference envelope, tranche-tagged constraint set, release-trigger schedule, contamination-audit plan, committed anti-drift witness). `brief-gatekeeper.md` at the exercise-provenance root.
specifications/reference-validation-v1.md:239:2. Confirm Session 014's provenance contains the full deliberation (`01-deliberation.md`), four perspective raw outputs, and the three decisions (D-069, D-070, D-071).
