provenance/012-methodology-naming/01-deliberation.md:159:3. **`specifications/identity.md` only as preferred placement, with concrete proposed file text** [01d, Q4]. The Outsider proposed the specific file contents (header "Methodology Identity", canonical-name line, provenance pointer). This placement mechanic — single-purpose identity record, no kernel v-bump, explicit supersession path — is the form the synthesis recommends for Q4. The Skeptic's (overruled-conditional) placement convergence with identity.md-only supports this but the Outsider's version specifies the file's text; the Skeptic's frames it as lightest-available-under-protest.
