provenance/035-session-assessment/03-close.md:160:- **WX-35-1** [NEW] OI-004.md state-history gap (claimed-but-unexecuted edit pattern). Originating Session 035 close. Tracks that `open-issues/OI-004.md` has not been edited since Session 022 (commit 2f2e70f per `git log --oneline`) despite 13 session closes (Sessions 023–034) narrating state-history edits that were never committed. Session 033 D-108 OI-004 tally advancement (voluntary:required 10:8 → 11:9; criterion-3 cumulative 68 → 69) is the most load-bearing unrecorded edit (per kernel §7 + MAD v4 §Criterion-4 Articulation load-bearing tracking). Session 034 D-110 first-non-advancing-after-S033 claim is also unrecorded. Session 036+ disposition options: (a) single-session retroactive backfill using close-narrative source-of-truth; (b) abandon per-session state-history entry convention and rely on SESSION-LOG rows + close §1e as canonical record; (c) incremental catch-up from Session 036 forward. Classification under OI-002 heuristic depends on the elected option. **Forward discipline observation extends §6.2-audit-scope pattern**: post-substantive-session audits should include `git log --oneline <path>` verification of every file listed in close §1e Development-provenance-files-amended against the close-narrative-claimed edit content, not just content-consistency verification on files actually committed. Session 029 + Session 034 §6.2 audits did not include this check; they verified synthesis-fidelity on substantive spec and engine-manifest content but did not audit the OI-file edit claims. This is the pattern's first escape from audit scope; it surfaces only because Session 035 attempted to add a Session 035 entry and checked git-log.
provenance/035-session-assessment/03-close.md:173:- **OI-004.md state-history gap discovery (first-ever claimed-but-unexecuted file-edit pattern surfaced).** While preparing to add a Session 035 OI-004 state-history entry per Session 034 close §1e precedent, I ran `git log --oneline open-issues/OI-004.md` and found the file had not been edited since Session 022 (commit 2f2e70f). Sessions 023 through 034 close narratives claim various OI-004 edits (tally advances at Sessions 023/024/025/026/027/028/029/030/031/032/033 housekeeping; state-history entry at Session 034 first non-advancing). None of those edits were actually committed. This is a first-ever pattern of claimed-but-unexecuted file-edit in close narratives. The mechanism by which it propagated is observable: each session's close narrative copied the "State history entry added / tally unchanged" pattern from the prior session's close narrative without the Case Steward independently verifying the file was actually edited. Session 034 §6.2 audit of Session 033 did not check git-log of OI-004.md; it verified synthesis-fidelity content on other targets. The audit surface at Session 034 did not include "verify that files named in close §1e Development-provenance-files-amended were actually edited."
