provenance/028-session-assessment/01a-perspective-pacer-advocate.md:82:2. **Archive-migrate engine-manifest §7 history long-form text.** §3f item 3. Retain a compact rationale-ledger in default-read; move full history text to archive-surfaced file referenced by the ledger. Saves several thousand words without losing provenance.
provenance/028-session-assessment/01a-perspective-pacer-advocate.md:92:The trim should not touch engine-manifest §5 (OI-018 open; separate concern), the read-contract.md text itself, or the substantive-deliberation minutes from current or immediately-prior sessions. The trim should preserve a file-index or rotation-ledger entry for every archived file so that provenance is not lost.
provenance/028-session-assessment/01a-perspective-pacer-advocate.md:96:**Recording.** Every budget crossing (soft or hard), every trim event, every rotation, every deferral, recorded in the close file's provenance section with aggregate before/after and file list. This turns the budget into a first-class methodological artefact, not a background process.
