provenance/012-methodology-naming/03-close.md:93:- **Brief-priming-absent for the fifth consecutive session.** The raw outputs show no unambiguous brief-seeded lexical echo. Brief-sourced terms appearing in raw outputs ("the methodology", "nine activities", "provenance", "self-hosting", "external artefact") are expected because they are load-bearing context. Novel contributions that are not brief-seeded include "selvedge / self-edge" (Outsider Q2), "sediment / sedimentum" (Steward Q2), "attachment failure mode" (Skeptic Q1-Q5), "friction-tax" (Steward Q5), "Claude-vocabulary overfitting" (Outsider Q2 cross-training flag), "mostly-Claude-process maturity risk" (Outsider Q5). Discipline continues; confirmed.
