provenance/011-w1-kernel-read-revision/00-assessment.md:64:**(E) OI-004 closure deliberation.** Criterion 4 ("articulate substantively different training provenance; enumerate acceptable participant kinds") unmet. Criteria 1–3 satisfied. The closure deliberation would itself be D-023_4-triggering. G satisfied (closure is the methodology's biggest self-validation question for external use). K satisfied (closed OI-004 is visible externally as a maturity marker). S satisfied (closes OI-004). O partially satisfied (downstream benefit to external application is indirect). **Scope objection:** OI-004 closure requires articulating a definition that the specification explicitly defers to "a successor decision." The articulation itself is a substantive piece of methodological theory — several hours of deliberation, careful wording that will likely bind future methodology claims. A "proceed with another item" session where the primary work bounced is not the right moment for the methodology's largest outstanding self-validation commitment.
