provenance/033-session-assessment/01d-perspective-outsider.md:82:Grandfather note: produced artefacts already labelled `validation: reference-validated` should not be silently relabelled. Either they remain at their original label with a footnote pointing to the v3 label change, or the relabel is explicit in their provenance. Silent rewriting of historical labels would be exactly the kind of soft drift the re-opening machinery is supposed to catch.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:31:This workspace is building a domain-general design methodology in which diverse perspectives deliberate, produce durable specifications, and preserve the reasoning behind decisions (provenance) so that future readers — human or agent — can reconstruct not just what was decided but what was considered and why. The methodology is self-hosting: it evolves by applying its own process to itself.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:89:- **Vocabulary distance.** Is the domain's vocabulary native to the methodology's existing specs and provenance, or genuinely external? Too-close domains risk confirmation bias; too-far domains risk the methodology's abstractions not translating.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:96:- **Methodology kernel.** Do the nine activities translate cleanly to external work? Is any activity under-specified for non-self application (e.g., Read: the workspace has finite prior provenance; an external domain may have none or too much)?
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:97:- **Workspace structure.** Does `specifications/` and `provenance/` translate? Would external application need a new top-level directory (`domains/`, `applications/`, or similar)?
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:107:- **OI-004 criterion 4** — articulating what "substantively different training provenance" means. This advances OI-004 closure irrespective of the 2-of-3 tally.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:135:Your response will be committed verbatim as provenance. It will be read by synthesis in conjunction with three other perspective responses. Your positions — including positions you hold reluctantly or conditionally — are load-bearing. Do not soften them to anticipate synthesis; record them at their strongest. If you hold a position in tension with your role-specific stance, record that tension explicitly; the synthesis prefers honest tension to performed alignment.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:141:You are **The Outsider**. Per `multi-agent-deliberation.md` v3's Non-Claude Participation mechanism (D-021 Shape A), you are included as a perspective indistinguishable in role from the three Claude perspectives except that your training lineage is outside the Claude model family. Open Issue OI-004 tracks whether convening distinct-training-provenance perspectives produces outcomes different from a Claude-only deliberation; your participation contributes to the sustained-practice tally whether or not your conclusions differ from the Claude perspectives' conclusions.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:153:The methodology is explicit that your inclusion tests a hypothesis (that distinct training provenance produces distinct reasoning on load-bearing questions). Whether the hypothesis is confirmed or disconfirmed here, your honest reasoning is the data the methodology needs.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:156:Reasoning from the brief only, without reading workspace files as instructed. I’m answering the six design questions directly and keeping the argument explicit so it can stand as provenance.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:174:I reject pure user-direction as the sole mechanism because it can create another deferral loop if the user gives only broad or ambiguous direction. The methodology needs a protocol that keeps momentum even when the user delegates judgment. I reject a dedicated multi-agent target-selection session as the primary path because it risks becoming more methodology-about-methodology at exactly the point where the methodology should be touching external work. Multi-agent deliberation is justified when a design choice is load-bearing; it is less justified when used to avoid taking a bounded, accountable step. I reject criteria-first with no required next action because it merely formalizes postponement. And I reject unilateral proposal without prior criteria because it weakens provenance: later readers would see a pick, but not the standard by which it was picked.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:182:By domain type, the best first candidates are software design, small research-plan design, curriculum design, or internal process design. These domains have a useful property: they admit explicit outputs and reasonably legible validation analogues. A software design can be checked for coherence and testability; a research plan can be checked for hypotheses, methods, and feasibility; a curriculum can be checked for sequencing and assessment coverage. Policy, physical systems, and high-stakes organizational redesign are worse first targets because the consequences are larger, the empirical feedback loops are slower, and the methodology’s first failure would be harder to interpret. Creative work is not impossible, but as a first test it creates validation ambiguity too early.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:192:The nine activities appear to translate cleanly enough from the brief alone. Read becomes “gather and bound the available domain inputs.” Assess becomes “determine whether the problem fits the methodology’s current scope.” Convene, Deliberate, Decide, Produce, Validate, Record, and Close all map naturally to external work. The likely stress points are not missing activities but under-specified interpretations. Read may be difficult when external domains have either almost no prior provenance or too much. Validate may be harder where the analogue of a test is less obvious than in software. But those are exactly the kinds of hidden assumptions a first application should reveal.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:194:I also do not think a new top-level directory such as `applications/` is required before first use. Existing `specifications/` and `provenance/` are probably sufficient for one trial. A new structural layer should be earned by demonstrated need, not introduced speculatively. Likewise, I would not revise the multi-agent or validation specs pre-emptively just because their phrasing may be somewhat self-referential. Let the first external application identify where wording actually breaks.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:200:My answer to Q1 is that continued general self-work is no longer justified. But if Session 007 nevertheless stays internal, only one self-increment would be defensible: a narrowly scoped first-application launch protocol. Not OI-001 naming, not OI-007 issue-format scaling, not OI-011 intra-family model mixing, and not OI-004’s remaining provenance criterion. Those may all matter eventually, but none of them addresses the structural uncertainty now dominating the methodology: how it crosses from self-hosting into first external use without either arbitrariness or further drift.
provenance/007-external-application-examination/01d-perspective-outsider.md:239:I reject pure user-direction as the sole mechanism because it can create another deferral loop if the user gives only broad or ambiguous direction. The methodology needs a protocol that keeps momentum even when the user delegates judgment. I reject a dedicated multi-agent target-selection session as the primary path because it risks becoming more methodology-about-methodology at exactly the point where the methodology should be touching external work. Multi-agent deliberation is justified when a design choice is load-bearing; it is less justified when used to avoid taking a bounded, accountable step. I reject criteria-first with no required next action because it merely formalizes postponement. And I reject unilateral proposal without prior criteria because it weakens provenance: later readers would see a pick, but not the standard by which it was picked.
