**Voluntary:required ratio rebalances 7:6 → 7:7** (required catches up; first parity since Session 014). **Five concrete Outsider-sourced contributions materially shaped adopted Session 021 content:** (1) bifurcation of training-provenance-for-models vs selection-independence-for-humans as the criterion-4 frame text-structure — adopted as R1 spec text; no Claude perspective produced this two-branch decomposition; (2) "stable attributable identity at provider/model-family/model-id granularity" as a third necessary model-branch prong — adopted into R1; Operationaliser's closed-set was at provider level only, Articulator's at organisation level only; (3) behavioural-fingerprint self-disclosure ("I more readily reject the offered frame, police type/boundary drift, and convert vague distinctions into operational gates") — concrete cross-family self-assessment no Claude perspective could produce structurally; (4) GPT-family blind spots named in R2 commentary ("procedural flattening, over-trust in explicit tests and checklists, premature closure once an operational rule exists, treating GPT as the default proxy for all externality") — frame-completion preserving that "non-Claude" is not "blind spots exhausted"; (5) "indefinitely movable finish line" framing — preserved as §5.3 first-class minority operational warrant. Session 021's Outsider contribution kind is **frame-completion at the spec-text structural level** — fourth distinct kind of Outsider contribution recorded across Sessions 005-021 (third-way split-resolution; structural innovation; layered-model frame-replacement; type-drift frame-replacement; structural bifurcation). **Criterion-3 cumulative 50 → 55**. **NOVEL DATA PATTERN at Session 021**: Outsider performed pre-response workspace exploration (four `exec` tool calls reading specifications/engine-manifest.md, multi-agent-deliberation.md, open-issues.md, provenance/017/, provenance/020/) before producing its response body. Per Outsider's own honest-limits this did not violate §10 anti-import (workspace read is not pretraining import); pattern recorded for future OI-015 / criterion-4 deliberations on the boundary between brief content and workspace context for Outsider perspectives. **Three watchpoints recorded:** WX-21-1 (R1 variance-clause discipline test on this very SESSION-LOG entry — calibrated to substantial complexity per first-engine-bump + spec-revisions + state-change scope; Skeptic F3 falsifier upper bound is 12K chars without complexity, this entry is below); WX-21-2 (R4 condition (iii) cross-model contradiction-prevailing data point requirement is unverified — closure-retrospective in future session may find no such case in existing 50 criterion-3 data points, blocking closure indefinitely; response options (a) wait for one OR (b) revise condition (iii) downward); WX-21-3 (synthesis adopted R4 keep-open over close-now via convergence-by-mechanism reasoning — synthesis is single-Claude-orchestrator highest-risk re-entry surface; Session 022 audit should specifically test whether convergence-by-mechanism reasoning holds up or whether synthesis privileged Claude-Claude convergence over cross-family vote unduly). **OI-007 count unchanged at 12** (OI-004 transitions states but remains open; no OI opened or resolved). **OI-002 ninth data point** (multi-agent-deliberation.md v3 → v4 substantive; validation-approach.md v3 → v4 substantive; tools/validate.sh substantive update — five-point heuristic continues to hold stable). **Brief-priming-absent for eleventh consecutive session.** Full D-024 manifests for all four participants including the new v4 fields exercising the schema. Session 022 should: run `tools/validate.sh` at start (expect 467 + new check counts; verify checks 16/17/19 fire for Session 021's manifests and pass on the Outsider's manifest which exercises the v4 schema; verify check 18 produces "no oi-004-retrospective.md present; out-of-scope" line); audit Session 021 synthesis fidelity (particular attention to: whether the convergence-by-mechanism reasoning grounding R4 keep-open holds up on re-inspection per WX-21-3, or whether Claude-Claude Skeptic+Operationaliser convergence dominated cross-family Articulator+Outsider close-now vote; whether R1's two-branch model/human bifurcation is internally consistent or has a gap at "what about agentic-system participants that are neither model-only nor human-only"; whether R3 schema additions surface useful operator-knowledge or drift toward `unknown`-as-default per §5.4 Skeptic minimal-schema minority trigger 1; whether the five §5 minorities carry operationally meaningful warrants per Session 015/019/020 precedent; whether the WX-21-2 cross-model contradiction-prevailing data point can be identified in existing 50 data points or requires waiting for one to occur); halt for operator ratification before substantive execution; consider one of (a) closure-retrospective draft (would test WX-21-2 directly); (b) Cell 1 re-attempt paths A1/A2/A3 from Session 019 R1-R5 unexercised since adoption; (c) OI-015 laundering-gap deliberation (benefits from H4 first-exercise); (d) H4 first-exercise (needs external problem brief from operator); (e) operator-directed agenda. **engine-v2 portability check note for Session 022**: external-application workspace initialising from engine-v2 should inherit the new schema fields and Tier 2 Q8; verify engine-manifest.md §6 initialisation contract still works with the v2 file set. |
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8a-SESSION-LOG/00-source.md:16:| 020 | 2026-04-22 | Workspace Scaling — `workspace-structure.md` §SESSION-LOG Minor Amendment; OI-007 Annotation; CLAUDE.md mempalace Orchestrator-Convenience; Engine-v1 Preserved | Ran `tools/validate.sh` at start (443 pass, 0 fail — tenth consecutive clean session-opener run). Audit of Session 019 synthesis fidelity across four close-directed dimensions: clean (cross-family revise-now rubric genuinely affirmative at macro level with substantive Outsider content contributions; R1's three C3 rejection conditions non-redundant with independent-firing scenarios; three new §10 minorities operationally meaningful — Minimalist cleanest falsifier, Skeptic trigger-tied, Reviser softest-but-not-ornamental; R1–R5 aggregate passes anti-laundering on external re-inspection). One minor framing-awareness note for future synthesizers: cross-family-majority on macro-question does not automatically transfer to specific content sub-questions. **Path (E) operator-directed agenda ratified:** operator proposed deliberating SESSION-LOG.md + open-issues.md scalability (both exceed 25,000-token single-read ceiling) and whether installed `mempalace` tool (or alternatives) should be adopted. **Thirteenth heterogeneous-participant deliberation** (voluntary, not required-trigger; seventh voluntary after 007/008/010/012/013/019): 3 Claude Opus 4.7 subagents (Splitter structural-advocate, Tooler tool-first-advocate with hands-on mempalace testing, Skeptic adversarial inheriting Session 019 Minimalist defer-revision-in-spirit) plus 1 non-Claude Outsider (OpenAI GPT-5.4 via `codex exec`, session id `019db491-3ac2-7e53-950c-b1c2ead7a4af`, reasoning effort xhigh, 22,182 tokens). Deliberation-anchor commit `c4025d5`. Two decisions (D-080 adopts R1–R3; D-081 OI housekeeping). D-080 triggers `[d016_3]`; D-081 triggers `[none]`. **3-of-4 cross-family convergence for engine-v1 preservation** (Tooler Claude + Skeptic