nal warrant: OI-housekeeping failure from segment-read, count-tally disagreement with git, 50K-token file ceiling); Splitter per-session-file directory for SESSION-LOG (§5.2 with three-item warrant: 12K-char entry without complexity per Skeptic F3, single-read ceiling breach within 5 sessions, reasoning error traceable to segmented-read); Outsider restore-to-brief-index (§5.3 with three-item warrant: citation laundering vs 03-close.md, variance-clause invoked beyond complexity bound, ceiling breach despite variance-clause); Skeptic defer-entirely on mempalace (§5.4 with four-item warrant: non-use within 3 sessions, search-laundering incident, version drift, external-application confusion). **OI-004 tally unchanged at 6-of-3** (voluntary non-advancing per Sessions 007/008/010/012/013/019 precedent — no d023_* fires on D-080's `[d016_3]`). **Voluntary:required ratio 6:6 → 7:6** (voluntary now exceeds required). **Five concrete Outsider-sourced contributions materially shaped adopted content:** (1) "indexes drifted to dossiers" type-drift frame-challenge diagnosis; (2) scan-surface-vs-detail-surface separation principle shaping R1's canonical-detail pointer; (3) strict-sequential minimum-viable-change ordering shaping §5 minority activation warrants; (4) portability-loss argument against engine-definition tool adoption (cross-family independent from Skeptic's Markdown-+-shell-script argument); (5) semantic-retrieval staleness pretraining-sourced concern corroborated by Tooler hands-on. Criterion-3 cumulative **55** across Sessions 005–020 (50 through Session 019; 5 added in Session 020). Criterion-4 remains unmet. **Second frame-replacement Outsider contribution in history** — establishes pattern of two instances (Session 017 H4 layered model; Session 020 type-drift) noted for future criterion-4-articulation deliberation. **WX-20-1 watchpoint:** R3's reliance on orchestrator discipline to treat mempalace output as candidate-discovery-only is the session's weakest-bonded mitigation; activation trigger is first search-laundering incident (orchestrator cites mempalace output not verifiable against source via Read). **OI-016 unchanged:** Resolved-provisional; seven re-opening triggers in `reference-validation.md` v2 §9; no trigger fires on Session 020 actions. **OI-007 count unchanged at 12**; no OI opened or resolved (four new first-class minorities held at `01-deliberation.md` §5 per Session 015/016/019 precedent). **OI-015 positive example:** operator input surfaced explicitly per brief §2; perspectives treated it as input not fact; kernel §1 domain-reading reconciliation clause operated as intended. **Brief-priming-absent for tenth consecutive session.** Full D-024 manifests for all four participants. Session 021 should: run `tools/validate.sh` at start; audit Session 020 synthesis fidelity (particular attention to: whether the 3-of-4 cross-family engine-v1-preservation rubric genuinely honoured cross-family weighting; whether R1's variance-clause bounding is strong enough to prevent unbounded drift in Session 021+'s own SESSION-LOG entry; whether R3's CLAUDE.md paragraph treats mempalace caveats as load-bearing-honesty or as ornamental disclaimers; whether the four first-class minorities at §5 carry operationally meaningful warrants; whether the Outsider type-drift diagnosis reading is defensible on re-inspection or whether Session 020 should have adopted restoration-direction); open under no default pre-commitment; consider one of (a) Cell 1 re-attempt with S1 (Feldenkrais Pelvic Clock) or S2 (Alexander Semi-Supine) under revised two-stage C3 — direct test of R1–R5 effectiveness from Session 019; (b) Cell 1 re-attempt with fresh re-survey (lower-saturation pool; multi-session scope likely); (c) OI-004 closure criterion-4 articulation (D-023-triggering; non-Claude required; single-session fit); (d) OI-015 laundering-gap deliberation (benefits from H4 first-exercise); (e) first-exercise of H4 application-initialisation (needs ext