provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8a-SESSION-LOG/00-source.md:20:| 016 | 2026-04-22 | Operator Reframing Input — OI-017 Opened; D-072 Preserved | Ran `tools/validate.sh` at start (363 pass, 0 fail — seventh consecutive clean session-opener run). Session 016 received a session-open operator input (preserved verbatim at `provenance/016-operator-reframing-assessment/00-operator-input.md`) proposing a **structural reframing**: the workspace may be better understood as an **engine** (defined inputs, procedures, outputs) rather than as a methodology in the abstract. Two structural consequences offered as input rather than direction: (1) distinguishability of the engine's executable definition from development provenance; (2) distinct execution prompts for different applications of the engine. Operator explicitly stated resolution is not required this session; any file including PROMPT.md may be modified; tools may be installed via `uv tool`; agenda to be determined accordingly. Audit of Session 015 synthesis fidelity: clean on both auditable dimensions (four cited raw-output line references in `015-session-assessment/00-assessment.md` §2 all verified against Session 014 files; D-072 `[none]` triggers declaration consistent with decision's content per Q7). **Single-perspective session** (no deliberation; scope-appropriate per Session 015 D-072 precedent — this is a surveying + hypothesising response to operator input, not an originated design output). Per PROMPT.md anti-silent-import rule and OI-015 laundering-enforcement requirement, operator input surfaced through explicit §3 surveying step (six related framings across traditions — closest fit: interpreter-vs-interpreted-program) and §4 hypothesising step (three competing hypotheses H1 no reframing / H2 full reframing / H3 partial reframing, each with gains, losses, strongest-advocate-position-hypothesised). Surveying identified the word "methodology" is used in two distinct senses across the active specifications (abstract-approach vs. concrete-implementation) — a latent ambiguity now surfaced for deliberation. **One decision (D-073)** declaring `**Triggers met:** [none]` with triggers rationale: ratifies Option α (assessment-only; defer Cell 1; open OI-017); preserves D-072 precommitment with re-disposition (Session 017 default is Cell 1 per D-072 unless user elects OI-017 deliberation first). **OI-017 opened** (engine-vs-methodology reframing): activation trigger "first session electing to deliberate"; preferred starting point H1/H2/H3 frame with explicit permission for additional hypotheses; D-023-triggering deliberation requires non-Claude participation (kernel revision is possible under H2/H3; PROMPT.md revision is significant-event per workspace-structure.md). **OI-017 is the first open issue surfaced from external operator input rather than from the methodology's own self-deliberation** — a novel origin kind recorded in OI-007 annotation. OI-007 count 12 → 13. **No spec changes; no external artefact; no OI state changes beyond OI-017 opening** (OI-016 remains Resolved-provisional; OI-004 tally 5-of-3 unchanged; criterion-3 cumulative 40; voluntary:required ratio 5:5 unchanged). No new watchpoints opened (OI-007 scaling pressure argues against redundant WX-16-\*; audit findings tracked within OI-017 or §2). No tool installation exercised (operator `uv tool` authorisation recorded but not needed this session); no PROMPT.md revision exercised (operator revision-authorisation recorded but single-perspective revision would be specification violation per workspace-structure.md significant-event rule; deferred to OI-017 deliberation). OI-009 G/O/K/S evaluation passes all four criteria (external-frame translation + external-action-decision-space narrowing + external-reader visibility + specific-obstacle resolution). Session 016 work-shape extends Session 007 (external-application preparation) and Session 015 (reference-validation agenda ratification) precedents for legitimate planning-only session-shape responding to external input. Session 017 should: run `tools/validate.sh` at start; audit Session 016 synthesis fidelity (narrower surface — verify §2 Session-015 audit consistency; verify §3 word-usage survey accurate across specifications; verify D-073 `[none]` declaration consistency; verify OI-017 activation trigger and preferred starting point operationally meaningful); execute Option A Cell 1 per D-072 default unless user steers to OI-017 deliberation first. OI-017 deliberation path (if ratified): convene 3–4 perspectives with at least one adversarial Skeptic (inheriting Session 012 refuse-to-name minority is natural) plus one non-Claude Outsider per D-023_1; deliberate H1/H2/H3 with permission for additional hypotheses; decision venue for any PROMPT.md revision, kernel revision, or new `engine-manifest.md` specification creation. |
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8a-SESSION-LOG/00-source.md:21:| 015 | 2026-04-22 | Reference-Validation Agenda Ratified; First-Exercise Deferred | Ran `tools/validate.sh` at start (353 pass, 0 fail). Audit of Session 014 synthesis fidelity against the four close-directed questions: **one substantive new-eyes finding** — the Session 014 close's claim that "Cell-2 iteration budget mitigates Architect's continuous-loop concern" overstates; Cell-2 iteration addresses within-session emergent-constraint responsiveness, not the cross-session validation-to-Produce feedback loop Architect's raw Q3 actually targeted. WX-14-2 remains correctly scoped to Architect's actual concern; only the close's Honest-Notes paraphrase is loose. Three other findings: 2-2 OI-016 disposition cross-model+adversarial convergence genuine (Skeptic's evidence-kind argument and Outsider's narrower-claim argument independently load-bearing; third occurrence of Skeptic+Outsider alignment against Claude-majority); Skeptic's "provisional substitute" content captured via anti-substitution clause + scope-statement but structural framing rejected (live question parked behind OI-016 trigger 6); `reference-validation.md` §1 eight-criterion list executable in principle, pool-survival under C3+C5+C8 tension is first-exercise empirical question. **Single-perspective session** (no deliberation; scope-appropriate per user-ratified planning-only work-shape — the audit is cross-scope examination of four raw perspective files plus Session 014 close, not a cross-perspective deliberation; kernel §3 adversarial-perspective requirement is scoped to "deliberative work where decisions will be made" and applies to originated designs, not user-ratification implementations). User ratification received verbatim: *"Apply defaults and your recommendations, but do not proceed with producing a mixed shortlist in this session, leave it an open item."* **One decision (D-072)** declaring `**Triggers met:** [none]` with triggers rationale — no kernel change, no spec revision, no OI-004 state change, no novel multi-perspective design output. Defaults locked in: mixed-direction shortlist (same-domain-adjacent + different-domain-representative); orchestrating agent as Case Steward with `reference-validation.md` §4 L2 known-limitation flag for inclusion in eventual `contamination-audit.md`; Stop 3b session shape (Cell 1 + Cell 2 within Session N per spec default), with user-ratification halt between selection-shortlist and seal commit. Reference-case shortlist production deferred to Session 016+ as carried-forward work (not opened as new OI per Session 007 D-044 precedent; OI-007 count unchanged at 12). **No spec changes; no external artefact; no OI state changes** (OI-016 remains Resolved-provisional; OI-004 tally 5-of-3 unchanged; criterion-3 cumulative 40; voluntary:required ratio 5:5 unchanged). No new watchpoints opened (audit finding tracked as WX-14-2 with corrected scoping; OI-007 scaling pressure argues against redundant WX-15-\*). Session 015 work-shape is analogous to Session 007's external-application-preparation — legitimate preparation-only session-shape without deliberation. Session 016 should: run `tools/validate.sh` at start; audit Session 015 synthesis fidelity with narrower surface (verify §2 raw-output citation consistency; verify D-072 `[none]` declaration consistency); execute Option A Cell 1 per `reference-validation.md` §3 unless user steers otherwise — source 3–5 candidate reference cases spanning mixed direction; run the C3 saturation gate and L1 contamination canary on each; present surviving shortlist for user ratification of single candidate; seal case pack per Cell 1 outputs with anti-drift witness commit; proceed to Cell 2 Produce if budget permits; engage six OI-016 re-opening triggers as operational commitment. |
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/01b-perspective-minimalist.md:46:> Artefacts produced by a session for use outside the workspace are placed in that session's provenance directory alongside its deliberation and decisions, unless a future session names a reason to do otherwise.
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/01b-perspective-minimalist.md:48:Session 008's artefact at `provenance/008-first-external-application/artefact-morning-unfurl.md` stays where it is. No move, no copy, no symlink, no forward pointer.
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/01b-perspective-minimalist.md:50:**Rejected: new top-level `applications/` directory.** One artefact is one data point. Creating `applications/` from one case makes a pattern claim the evidence does not support. If Sessions 010, 012, and 015 each produce external artefacts, and the provenance-embedded placement starts to strain — e.g., artefacts get referenced across sessions, or users want to find them without knowing which session produced them — *then* `applications/` earns its slot. Premature top-level directories are expensive to retract: once specified, later sessions defer to them even when the fit is poor.
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/01b-perspective-minimalist.md:52:**Rejected: hybrid (artefact in provenance + forward-pointer stub in a top-level location).** A stub file in a directory that does not yet exist is worse than no stub — it creates a directory whose only function is to hold pointers, which is a structural commitment disguised as minimalism. If `applications/` is not worth creating, its stub-precursor is not worth creating either.
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/01b-perspective-minimalist.md:54:**Rejected: rename or move the Session 008 artefact.** Session 008's provenance is closed; moving files out of a closed session violates the "immutable once the session closes" property spelled out in the current workspace-structure text. Even if the move were technically allowed, it would be churn for no gain. The Session 008 artefact is findable by anyone who reads Session 008's session-log entry, which is where external readers will land.
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/01b-perspective-minimalist.md:72:Open issue wording (brief): *The hard-coded `02-decisions.md` path in checks 14–15 of `tools/validate.sh` constrains session provenance file numbering. Workaround: non-decisions artefacts use non-numbered filenames. Revisit if numbering pressure becomes a recurring issue.*
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/01b-perspective-minimalist.md:142:(a) **Position I expect to differ from others:** I expect the Architect or the Methodology-Fit perspectives to propose `applications/` or an elaboration spec for external-artefact Validate. I hold, reluctantly, that both are premature. One data point is one data point; every additional spec-surface will itself need to be validated. If synthesis adopts a larger structure, I want the provenance to show that the minimal alternative was on the table and defensible, not absent. (b) **Suspect assumption:** the brief treats "the user reported back" as the prototype of domain-native Validate. Session 008's artefact had a user whose stiffness was in scope that morning. Other external artefacts may not have such a timely, specific, single-user receipt loop. The Q1 bullet I propose inherits this assumption; I flagged the watchpoint in Q4. (c) **Framing concern:** the brief's ratified scope is narrow, but each question invites a proposal; inviting proposals pulls against narrowness. I have tried to answer each Q with the minimum, including "do not do this" where warranted.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:83:   132	### provenance/
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:88:   137	/provenance/
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:97:   146	Each session's provenance is a numbered directory. Files within are numbered for reading order. All provenance files use Markdown with YAML frontmatter:
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:108:   157	Provenance records are **immutable** once the session closes. Errors or retractions are recorded in subsequent sessions, not by editing past records.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:110:   159	**Archive-pack subdirectory** (added v4): when a session's raw perspective file or other provenance file exceeds the default-read per-file budget (`specifications/read-contract.md` §2), the file is archive-packed before session close per `read-contract.md` §9. Archive-packs live at `provenance/NNN-title/archive/<slug>/` with `manifest.yaml` + numbered chunks. Retroactive migration of a closed session's over-budget file uses the copy-plus-reference discipline (Session 009 D-054 precedent): the archive-pack is created in the migrating session's provenance directory, not the originating session's directory, preserving D-017 immutability.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:129:   178	`NNN` is the producing session's number; `[slug]` is a short descriptive name. Filenames within the directory are descriptive (not numbered for reading order) — the numbered-reading-order convention applies to provenance records only.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:131:   180	External artefacts are **mutable**: they may be revised by later sessions in response to domain validation (see `methodology-kernel.md` §7 Domain validation) or other feedback. Revisions update the artefact in place; the revising session's provenance records what changed and why. When an artefact is revised, any corresponding copies in the originating session's provenance directory and in prior revising sessions' provenance remain untouched (per the provenance immutability rule) and serve as historical witnesses to earlier versions.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:133:   182	Each external artefact file includes in its frontmatter the fields `originating_session` (the session that first produced the artefact) and, when applicable, `regularized_in_session` (the session that moved the artefact into `applications/` after the fact) and `provenance_witness_path` (the path to the frozen provenance copy, if one exists). Subsequent revisions update `last-revised-session` in the frontmatter.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/08-chunk.md:135:   184	**Regularization of pre-existing external artefacts.** When an external artefact was placed in a producing session's provenance directory before `applications/` existed as a defined top-level directory, the artefact is regularized into `applications/` by **copy-plus-reference**: a copy is made to `applications/NNN-[slug]/[filename]` with the frontmatter fields above; the provenance copy is not moved, modified, or deleted. The regularizing session's decision record is the authoritative cross-reference.
