provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/09-chunk.md:46:**Reasoning:** WX-22-1 is the risk that archive/reference machinery ceases to be repair and becomes routine non-reading. Carrying the warning keeps default-read meaning simple: there is still one governing MAD file read in full at session open. No archive indirection is introduced, and no “secondary” spec is created that may be treated socially as optional even if formally default-read. This matters because the workspace already has one documented asymmetry between the spec and actual Outsider practice: MAD says perspectives reason from the brief and “do not read workspace files,” but Session 023 close records the Outsider’s stable pattern of pre-response workspace exploration and flags the mismatch as worth future attention ([multi-agent-deliberation.md](</Users/ericmccowan/Development/complex-systems-engine/specifications/multi-agent-deliberation.md:129>) lines 129-131, [provenance/023-session-assessment/03-close.md](</Users/ericmccowan/Development/complex-systems-engine/provenance/023-session-assessment/03-close.md:110>) lines 110-112). I do not want a budget-response split to freeze boundaries around a file that may soon need a different substantive repair.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/09-chunk.md:48:If a future A.2 split is taken, the discipline test must be concrete: Session 025’s open assessment should list both files explicitly in its default-read surface, the same way Session 024’s assessment lists every active spec now ([00-assessment.md](</Users/ericmccowan/Development/complex-systems-engine/provenance/024-session-assessment/00-assessment.md:12>) lines 12-19). If only the “core” file gets named and the OI-004 file becomes de facto consult-only, that is laundering. For A.3, the answer is harder: archive relocation of the OI-004 or heterogeneous-participant sections would make archive access routine, because validators and human auditors would need those sections repeatedly. That would be exactly the bad pattern WX-22-1 warns about.
provenance/024-session-assessment/archive/024-outsider/09-chunk.md:70:- Aggregate surface: record 89,327 words / 35 files at open, then record close delta. If the 90K advisory threshold is crossed at close, say explicitly whether that was driven by close verbosity rather than spec growth. Session 024’s own assessment already flags that risk ([00-assessment.md](</Users/ericmccowan/Development/complex-systems-engine/provenance/024-session-assessment/00-assessment.md:45>) lines 45-49).
