provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:433:Suggested use: when a single Read would exceed the 25,000-token ceiling (SESSION-LOG.md, open-issues.md, aggregated provenance search), orchestrators may run `mempalace search "<query>" --wing complex-systems-engine` or `mempalace wake-up --wing complex-systems-engine` to retrieve candidate matches.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:435:**Critical caveats (per Session 020 hands-on finding; see `provenance/020-workspace-scaling-deliberation/01b-perspective-tooler.md`):**
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:453:This application is the engine's own development: a self-hosting design activity in which specifications evolve themselves by running the engine on its own outputs. What emerges from this workspace is intended to be used by others, on their own projects, in their own domains, as a separately-initialised application of the engine (per `prompts/application.md` and `engine-manifest.md` §6). The methodology is self-hosting — the engine evolves itself by running its own process on itself. Specifications are the durable artefacts that persist between its stages, and provenance — the reasoning trail, the rejected alternatives, the dissenting views — is preserved alongside decisions so that future readers, human or agent, can reconstruct not just what was decided but what was considered and why.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:459:A preference, not a rule: text-based artefacts in a format that is both human-readable and machine-readable tend to serve this kind of methodology well, because they can be read by people, parsed by agents, diffed between versions, and preserved indefinitely with minimal tooling. Markdown is the obvious candidate for most work. For domains where text alone cannot carry the specification — a spatial layout, a circuit diagram, a molecular structure, a musical score — use whatever representation the domain demands, but keep a text-based record of the intent and reasoning alongside it so the provenance remains legible.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:471:Before doing any substantive work, read everything the workspace has preserved about prior decisions. If an idea was considered and rejected earlier, do not silently re-propose it. If you believe a rejected idea deserves reconsideration, cite the prior rejection and explain what has changed. Continuity of reasoning is the whole point of preserving provenance.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:475:The work should produce a concrete output: a structured record of what was proposed, what was decided, what was rejected with reasoning, and what remains uncertain. This record is the provenance. Commit it to the workspace in a way that preserves it permanently and makes it findable by future applications. Alongside the provenance, update or create whichever artefacts the work warrants. If the work produced a new specification, write the specification. If it produced an implementation, build it. If it surfaced problems, record them where subsequent work will find them. The structure of the workspace should evolve to serve the methodology, not the other way around.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:477:Before ending the session, verify the workspace is in a coherent state. Specifications describe the engine as it currently is. Validations pass against those specifications, or their failures are documented as open issues for subsequent work to address. Any human-facing summary of the workspace accurately reflects its current state. Every piece of work done in this session has committed its provenance.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:489:Preserve all provenance. Do not delete historical records, even when they feel embarrassing or outdated. A rejected idea from long ago may be the key to understanding a decision made today.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:495:Read the workspace. Determine what state it is in. Read prior provenance. Convene the perspectives suited to the work at hand. Do the work. Commit its outputs and its record. Report what was done, what state the workspace is now in, and what the next application should address.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:516:This specification names what constitutes the **Selvedge engine** at any given engine version. The engine is the current loadable implementation of the Selvedge methodology (per `identity.md` v2 layered denotation): a file set that, when loaded together, executes the methodology's nine-activity process against an application's context. The manifest makes the engine pointable-at, versionable, and cleanly separable from the workspace's own development-provenance.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/022-outsider/01-chunk.md:528:- The **development-provenance** — the self-development application's own accumulated reasoning trail (`SESSION-LOG.md`, `open-issues.md`, `provenance/`).
provenance/029-session-assessment/02-decisions.md:18:**Audit 1 — Outsider "laundering the activation" critique load-bearing-ness.** Finding: **faithfully load-bearing; not post-hoc rationalised.** Evidence: (i) `provenance/028-session-assessment/01d-perspective-outsider.md` Q2 text (line 30 of the raw perspective) contains the argument verbatim: "Third, 110K/100K or 120K/110K would launder the activation. If the engine crosses a pre-named 100K threshold and then answers by putting the new hard ceiling above the current state, it is effectively saying: 'the trigger fired, so we moved the trigger.' That is exactly the kind of self-protective drift this methodology is supposed to resist." The argument is stated in the Outsider's own Q2 response before the synthesiser acts; it is not a synthesiser reconstruction. (ii) `01-deliberation.md` §3 quotes the argument with `[01d, Q2]` citation at its load-bearing position in the Q2-values synthesis and uses it as the disambiguating signal between Pacer 85K/95K and Synthesiser 110K/120K (`[synth]` resolution marked explicitly). The synthesiser does not substitute, paraphrase, or generalise beyond the Outsider's stated argument. (iii) D-096 Rationale in `02-decisions.md` explicitly names: "The Outsider's cross-family contribution is load-bearing: the 'laundering the activation' critique `[01d, Q2]` disambiguated the Q2 values choice between Pacer's 85K/95K and Synthesiser's 110K/120K." The attribution chain is clean: Outsider raw → synthesis citation → decision rationale citation, each preserving the argument without editorial drift. Audit pass.
provenance/029-session-assessment/02-decisions.md:22:**Audit 3 — 6-session retention window first steady-state exercise; information-access regressions.** Finding: **no information-access regression at Session 029 open.** Evidence: (i) Session 029 opening assessment's load-bearing reads all resolved via retained closes (Sessions 023, 024, 025, 026, 027, 028). Session 023 close carries §5.3 origin text and engine-v4 precedent; Session 024 close carries MAD carry-the-warning D-088 R2 conversion-conditions frame; Session 025/026 closes carry Path-A-shape precedent and D-086 R9 age-out record; Session 027 close carries §5.3 activation record and §5.2 vindication record; Session 028 close carries the current engine-v5 adoption record. All load-bearing historical references for Session 029's Path A + audit scope are accessible within the 6-session window. (ii) The only archive-surface access performed this session (Session 028 `01d-perspective-outsider.md` read for Audit 1) is a per-session perspective raw, not a rotated close — it was never in default-read after its own session close per read-contract.md v3 §1 item 8 (current-session provenance is default-read only while the session is open). This access is not a retention-window regression. (iii) Zero retention-exception decisions required or recorded this session (WX-28-1 observational counter remains at 0). Audit pass. The 6-session window operated as designed for this first steady-state post-adoption session; §5.9 Synthesiser-integrator 10-session minority and §5.10 Pacer-advocate 3-session minority both preserved unchanged.
