provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8b-open-issues/00-source.md:21:**Session 008 tally (per D-052):** Session 008 included non-Claude participation (Outsider = OpenAI GPT-5 via `codex exec`, continuing the Sessions 005/006/007 pattern) with a full D-024 manifest, **but none of Session 008's decisions (D-050, D-051, D-052) triggered any D-023 clause** — target-selection and artefact-production did not modify the kernel or specs, and no OI-004 state change was asserted. Per the strict v3 spec closure-criterion-2 reading, Session 008's deliberation was not a required-trigger deliberation; the sustained-practice tally does **not** advance. Tally remains at 2 of 3. This is the **second consecutive non-advancing non-Claude session**. Criterion 3 gains three more data points from Session 008 (four-way Q5 convergence on "representability / document-shape / artefact-shape / medium bias" crossing the model-family axis — the Outsider's independent arrival at the same structural finding is the strongest single cross-model signal across all four heterogeneous sessions; Outsider's independent meal-rotation recommendation as Candidate 1 supporting synthesizer's shortlist composition; Outsider-unique "preference instability" failure-mode framing). Cumulative criterion-3 data points across Sessions 005–008: twelve. Criterion 4 (articulation of "substantively different training provenance") remains unmet.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8b-open-issues/00-source.md:29:**Session 012 tally (per D-065):** Session 012 included non-Claude participation (Outsider = OpenAI GPT-5 via `codex exec`, session id `019daa64-f24f-7402-be96-565c135009a1`, reasoning effort xhigh, 22,575 tokens) with a full D-024 manifest, **but none of Session 012's decisions (D-063, D-064, D-065) triggered any D-023 clause** — D-063 creates `specifications/identity.md` (not a D-023-listed spec family), D-064 closes OI-001 (not OI-004 — outside D-023.4's literal scope), D-065 records criterion-3 data additions without asserting tally advance. Per the strict v3 spec closure-criterion-2 reading and Session 007 D-049 / Session 008 D-052 / Session 010 D-059 precedent, Session 012's deliberation was not a required-trigger deliberation; the sustained-practice tally does **not** advance. Tally remains at 4 of 3. This is the **fourth non-advancing non-Claude session** after Sessions 007, 008, and 010. Criterion 3 gains five more data points from Session 012 (Outsider's cross-training divergence critique of internal-vocabulary compound names as name-family — meta-pattern critique no Claude perspective produced; Outsider-originated Selvedge candidate with self-edge etymology and three-trait metaphor — no Claude textile-metaphor produced; Outsider-originated `specifications/identity.md`-only placement with concrete proposed file text; Outsider-originated "light-touch canonical name: reference handle, not brand layer" Q1 framing that shaped identity.md scope; Outsider's mostly-Claude-process-maturity-risk asymmetry argument at Q5 shaping weighting of Skeptic's refuse-case). Cumulative criterion-3 data points across Sessions 005–012: **twenty-nine**. Criterion 4 (articulation of "substantively different training provenance") remains unmet. **Watchable pattern:** the voluntary-non-advancing count now equals the required-trigger count (4:4). For any future criterion-4-articulation or closure deliberation, this is evidence that the methodology's cross-model discipline is sustained roughly equally across required and voluntary inclusion rather than concentrated in required-trigger-only contexts.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8b-open-issues/00-source.md:37:**Session 019 tally (per D-079):** Session 019 included non-Claude participation (Outsider = OpenAI GPT-5.4 via `codex exec`, session id `019db44c-e6a3-7140-8aee-a0fdc1d44877`, reasoning effort xhigh, 26,112 tokens) with a full D-024 manifest, **but none of Session 019's decisions (D-078, D-079) triggered any D-023 clause** — D-078 revises `reference-validation.md` (not in D-023's enumerated list of kernel / `multi-agent-deliberation.md` / Tier 2 `validation-approach.md` revisions; D-078 carries `[d016_2, d016_3]` only) and does not assert an OI-004 state change; D-079 declares `[none]` per D-073/D-077 housekeeping precedent. Per the strict v3 spec closure-criterion-2 reading and Sessions 007/008/010/012/013 precedent, Session 019's deliberation was voluntary non-Claude participation without a required-trigger firing; the sustained-practice tally does **not** advance. Tally remains at 6-of-3. This is the **sixth non-advancing non-Claude session** after Sessions 007, 008, 010, 012, and 013. **Voluntary-to-required ratio rebalances from 5:6 to 6:6** (voluntary advances by 1; voluntary and required now even for the first time since Session 017). Criterion 3 gains **five concrete data points from Session 019**: (1) §4 L3 "not rescued by cleaner output from another family" pre-seal interpretation — no Claude perspective framed the anti-laundering path at this specific §4 L3 placement; (2) §9 trigger 6 extension closing the family-conditional-screening laundering route — no Claude perspective named this at this precision; (3) §1 C3 two-stage structural clarity with canary-as-early-warning-only framing shaping the adopted supplementary-vs-decisive distinction; (4) explicit naming / distinctive-sequence recovery as standalone rejection basis separate from percentage overlap; (5) screening/confirmatory-mismatch framing ([synth] testing-methodology import) justifying n=1 revision adoption against Minimalist's statistical-deferral argument. Cumulative criterion-3 data points across Sessions 005–019: **50** (45 through Session 017; 5 added in Session 019). Criterion 4 (articulation of "substantively different training provenance") remains unmet.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8b-open-issues/00-source.md:41:**Session 021 tally (per D-082):** Session 021 is the **seventh required-trigger deliberation** with non-Claude participation. D-082 substantively revises `multi-agent-deliberation.md` v3 → v4 (d023_2 fires); D-082 itself asserts an OI-004 state change from "Closable pending criterion-4 articulation" to "Articulated; awaiting closure-retrospective" (d023_4 fires). The Outsider (OpenAI GPT-5.4 via `codex exec`, session id `019db4d9-d3d1-76c3-b6b1-a6287d0b73af`, reasoning effort xhigh, 59,489 tokens) participated with a full D-024 manifest. **Five concrete Outsider-sourced contributions materially shaped adopted Session 021 content:** (1) bifurcation of "training provenance" (models) vs "selection independence" (humans) as the criterion-4 frame text-structure — no Claude perspective produced this two-branch decomposition; (2) "stable attributable identity at provider/model-family/model-id granularity" as a third necessary prong for the model branch — Operationaliser's closed-set was at provider level only; Articulator's at organisation level only; (3) behavioural-fingerprint self-disclosure ("I more readily reject the offered frame, police type/boundary drift, and convert vague distinctions into operational gates") — concrete cross-family self-assessment no Claude perspective could produce structurally; (4) GPT-family blind spots named ("procedural flattening, over-trust in explicit tests and checklists, premature closure once an operational rule exists, treating GPT as the default proxy for all externality") — frame-completion contribution preserving that "non-Claude" is not "blind spots exhausted"; (5) "indefinitely movable finish line" framing for closure decision — preserved as §5.3 first-class minority operational warrant. Tally advances from 6-of-3 to **7-of-3**. Criterion-3 cumulative data points across Sessions 005–021: **55** (50 through Session 019; 5 added in Session 021). **Voluntary:required ratio rebalances from 7:6 to 7:7** (required catches up with voluntary; first session-since-014 with even ratio). **NOVEL DATA PATTERN at Session 021**: Outsider performed pre-response workspace exploration (four `exec` tool calls reading specifications/engine-manifest.md, multi-agent-deliberation.md, open-issues.md, provenance/017/, provenance/020/) before producing its response body. This grounded the response in actual spec text rather than the brief's quoted excerpts; per Outsider's own honest-limits this did not violate §10 anti-import (workspace read is not pretraining import). Recorded for future OI-015 / criterion-4 deliberations on the boundary between brief content and workspace context for Outsider perspectives.
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8b-open-issues/00-source.md:47:- **Criterion 3 (recorded impact on outcomes):** satisfied. Cumulative data points: **fifty-five** across Sessions 005-021 (fifty through Session 019; five added in Session 021 — Outsider's bifurcation of training-provenance vs selection-independence; stable-identity prong; behavioural-fingerprint self-disclosure; GPT-family blind spots; "indefinitely movable finish line" framing). Criterion 3 has been satisfied since Session 005; Sessions 009, 010, 011, 012, 013, 014, 017, 019, 021 extend the evidence base.
