provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8b-open-issues/00-source.md:209:| OI-001: Naming the methodology | 2026-04-20 | 012 | Session 001 opened the question; eleven sessions of deferral. Session 012 deliberation produced a shortlist of three candidates (Selvedge, Sediment, Strata) after filtering out Claude-family internal-vocabulary compounds per Outsider's cross-training divergence flag. User ratified **Selvedge** (light-touch canonical name; textile metaphor, "self-edge"; accents self-hosting + preservation + multi-strand). Canonical placement: `specifications/identity.md` (new single-purpose v1 spec, `supersedes: none`). Skeptic's refuse-to-name minority position preserved as first-class dissent in `provenance/012-methodology-naming/01c-perspective-skeptic.md`; operationalised as four explicit Reopening conditions in `specifications/identity.md` (external adoption; cross-domain artefact threshold; kernel-stability threshold; external naming pushback). See D-063 (name adoption), D-064 (OI-001 closure), D-065 (OI housekeeping). |
provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8b-open-issues/00-source.md:211:| OI-017: Engine-vs-methodology reframing | 2026-04-22 | 017 | Session 016 opened the OI from operator session-open input proposing a structural reframing (engine-as-defined-inputs-procedures-outputs vs methodology-in-abstract). Session 017 resolved via **H4 layered model adoption** per D-074 — a novel fourth hypothesis proposed by the Outsider (OpenAI GPT-5.4 via `codex exec`) that the three Claude perspectives (Architect-for-H2, Operationalist-for-H3, Skeptic-for-H1) did not independently produce. H4 distinguishes three layers: **Selvedge** names the methodology (abstract-approach); **Selvedge engine** denotes the current loadable implementation enumerated in the new `specifications/engine-manifest.md`; **applications of the Selvedge engine** are specific runs (self-development or external-problem). Adopted changes: `identity.md` v1 → v2 (substantive; adds three-layer denotation; v1 preserved); `workspace-structure.md` v2 → v3 (substantive; adds file-class distinction; v2 preserved); new `engine-manifest.md` v1 (engine enumeration + versioning discipline + external-application initialisation contract); `methodology-kernel.md` v4 + minor scope-clarification sentence in §Purpose (no v-bump per OI-002 heuristic); minor scope-applicability sentences in `multi-agent-deliberation.md` v3 and `validation-approach.md` v3 (no v-bumps); **PROMPT.md split** into thin dispatcher + `prompts/development.md` (self-development executable prompt) + `prompts/application.md` (external-application template); `reference-validation.md` v1 unchanged. Three first-class minorities preserved with specific operational reopening warrants: Skeptic's H1 (activates if 3 consecutive Sessions 018+ revise H4 without external-adoption evidence); Operationalist's H3 (activates if prompts/development.md and prompts/application.md turn out to be nearly duplicate in practice); Architect's H2 (activates if the layered distinction collapses in practice — users treat Selvedge and Selvedge engine as interchangeable in all cases). Five concrete Outsider-sourced contributions materially shaped adopted content (layered H4 frame; "Selvedge engine" qualified phrase; thin-dispatcher PROMPT.md pattern; "engine's autobiography" activation rule; H1/H2/H3 frame-challenge at Q1). See D-074 (H4 adoption + spec revisions), D-075 (OI housekeeping). `provenance/017-oi017-reframing-deliberation/` contains full deliberation record with all four raw perspective files, synthesis, manifests, and close. |
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/02-decisions.md:84:   > `NNN` is the producing session's number; `[slug]` is a short descriptive name. Filenames within the directory are descriptive (not numbered for reading order) — the numbered-reading-order convention applies to provenance records only.
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/02-decisions.md:86:   > External artefacts are **mutable**: they may be revised by later sessions in response to domain validation (methodology-kernel.md §7 Domain validation) or other feedback. Revisions update the artefact in place; the revising session's provenance records what changed and why. When an artefact is revised, the corresponding provenance copies in the originating session and any prior revising sessions remain untouched (per the provenance immutability rule) and serve as historical witnesses to earlier versions.
provenance/009-external-validate-receipt/02-decisions.md:88:   > **Regularization of pre-existing external artefacts.** When an external artefact was placed in a producing session's provenance directory before `applications/` existed, the artefact is regularized into `applications/` by **copy-plus-reference**: a copy is made to `applications/NNN-[slug]/[filename]` with frontmatter fields `originating_session` and `regularized_in_session`; the provenance copy is not moved, modified, or deleted. The regularizing session's decision record is the authoritative cross-reference.
