provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/014-oi016-outsider/08-chunk.md:2:./SESSION-LOG.md:14:| 010 | 2026-04-20 | Second External Application — House Decision in Five Moves | Ran `tools/validate.sh` at start (214 pass, 0 fail). User ratified Direction 1 (second external application) and Candidate A variant (two-person household decision protocol for shelving/landscaping-scale decisions in the A$500 range). Audit of Session 009 synthesis fidelity: clean (four Q2/Q3 2-2-split resolutions honoured, Skeptic's "drop Q1 entirely" minority preserved verbatim, mutable/immutable convergence genuinely three-perspective independent, no brief-priming detected). **Sixth heterogeneous-participant deliberation** (voluntary, not required-trigger): 3 Claude Opus 4.7 subagents (Drafter precision-drafter, Mediator process-design, Skeptic adversarial) plus 1 non-Claude Outsider (OpenAI GPT-5 via `codex exec`, session id `019da870-4e49-7953-aaf9-572867d386fe`, reasoning effort xhigh, 10,706 tokens). Deliberation-anchor commit `22c5216`. 3 decisions (D-057 through D-059). D-057: adopt synthesis recommendations and produce the external artefact; 5-move sequential structure with pause permission between Moves 3 and 4; Outsider's hybrid voice resolution (second-person plural addressing with first-person example lines) resolves the 2-2 Claude split on person (Drafter+Skeptic "we" vs Mediator "you two"); Outsider-originated burden-cost asymmetry clause in Move 4; Outsider-originated title "A House Decision in Five Moves"; "Not this" section with four refusals (scoring matrix, written case, third-party call, cool-off rule) per Skeptic's meta-refusal argument. D-058: five Session 010 watchpoints recorded (WX-10-1 methodology-vocabulary leakage; WX-10-2 asynchronous/fragmented-use requirement, Outsider-unique; WX-10-3 aim-at-obsolescence success criterion, Skeptic-framed; WX-10-4 validation-signal under-power; WX-10-5 pattern: synthesizer adopts Outsider-originated third-way to resolve 2-2 Claude splits, second occurrence after Session 009 Q2). D-059: **OI-005 unblocks** (second external application complete; sub-activity deliberation now available for Session 011+); OI-004 tally unchanged at 3 of 3 (no D-023 trigger fired — no kernel change, no spec revision, no OI-004 state change); four more data points added to OI-004 closure criterion 3 (cumulative nineteen across Sessions 005-010); OI-012/013/014 monitor (none activate). **External artefact produced at applications/010-household-decision-protocol/house-decision-five-moves.md** — **first use-from-scratch of the `applications/` canonical path** introduced in Session 009 D-054. **Strongest cross-model contributions from Outsider:** four concrete outcome-shaping contributions (burden-cost asymmetry clause; hybrid voice; title; asynchronous-use structural requirement). **Brief-priming-absent for third consecutive session.** Full D-024 manifests for all 4 participants. External Validate of artefact is **out-of-session**: user and wife will try the protocol on a live decision and report back at Session 011 open. Session 011 should: receive user+wife report-back on House Decision in Five Moves (domain-function verification); audit Session 010 synthesis fidelity (particular attention to whether the 2-2 voice split resolution honoured Outsider's hybrid faithfully, whether the Skeptic's "no artefact" null-alternative is readable in the adopted artefact, and whether methodology-vocabulary leakage was actually avoided in the artefact body text); consider whether any watchpoint findings warrant spec/kernel revision deliberations; consider third external application or OI-001 methodology naming or OI-004 closure deliberation or W1 kernel Read-activity revision; OI-005 sub-activity deliberation now available as a fifth option. |
