provenance/043-session-assessment/01d-perspective-outsider.md:33:Call this: **the engine's warrant surface is closed against its operator's frame observations.** The operator can provide data (reference texts, external constraints) and directives (single-token path ratifications), but the operator's standing role as *frame critic of the engine* has no spec-level ingestion mechanism. It depends on operator persistence and on the Case Steward being willing to classify an expanded input as Path-PD-class. That is a real asymmetry.
provenance/043-session-assessment/01d-perspective-outsider.md:61:The operator's framing reveals a different need: **not periodic, but cross-sectional**. The engine's existing self-observation is session-local (each session reads the last 6 closes). It has no mechanism that reads across the distribution of session-shapes over full history and asks whether that distribution is the one the engine wants. Session 027's §C Archivist minority named this as "single-session self-audits cannot catch cross-sectional drift" — still preserved, still un-operationalised.
