provenance/041-session-assessment/03-close.md:255:- **Engine-v7 five-session preservation window matches engine-v4 exactly — via substantive content, not pure preservation.** Engine-v4 Sessions 024–027 were four Path-A-pure preservations + Session 028 bump; engine-v7 Sessions 037–040 were four Path-A or Path-L+A preservations + Session 041 substantive content (OI-004 closure). The substantive-content fifth session is structurally different from engine-v4's pattern — engine-v4's §5.3 activation warrant forced Session 028 bump; engine-v7 has no activation-warrant-driven bump on Session 041 horizon (D-126 minor spec update is documentary-not-substantive; engine-v7 preserved). This is a new engine-v cadence pattern: substantive content at the five-session preservation depth without bumping. §5.4 Session 022 cadence minority does not re-escalate per precedent chain.
