provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:12:I read the four candidate synthesis files and assess whether the P4 Assertion claim in §3 substantively holds at source:
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:33:3. **Contradiction vs augmentation vs completion**. **Substantive augmentation.** The three Claude shapes are not mutually exclusive with three-cell — they fit inside Cell 2 or across Cells 2–3 — but the separation-of-duties primary framing is absent from all three, and the synthesis adopts the Outsider's framing as the primary organiser. Clears the *"contradicts (or substantively augments)"* bar `[MAD v4 §Closure iii per brief §2]`.
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:47:1. **Claude-consensus characterisation**. Three Claude subagents (Reviser, Skeptic-preserver, Synthesiser) did not distinguish workspace-identity from engine-definition files. Reviser: pure structural-signature dispatch, no new class. Skeptic-preserver: no revision. Synthesiser: layered hybrid assuming MODE.md without reclassifying it `[036/01-deliberation.md §3b]`. **No Claude perspective produced the engine-definition-vs-workspace-identity distinction at the manifest level.**
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:57:**Cumulative strength for P4 Assertion?** Yes. Tier 2 Q8 tests *"the cited divergence shows the synthesis adopted a position that contradicts (or substantively augments) the Claude consensus, not merely supplemented it."* All four cases clear the "not merely supplemented" bar. S021 and S036 clear the stronger "adopts Outsider text as spec-text" bar. S017 clears the strongest "frame-replacement" bar.
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:59:Weakness to flag: in several cases the three Claude perspectives did not converge on a single position to be contradicted — they split three ways and the Outsider replaced the frame itself. Under a strict reading of "Claude-perspective consensus" as *"all three held X"*, S017 would register no consensus at all. Under the Tier 2 Q8 *"contradicts or substantively augments"* reading, all four cases pass cleanly. I recommend citing under the Tier 2 Q8 language.
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:63:**Q1 (retrospective adequacy)**. The §3 Qualifying Deliberations Table is substantively sufficient. Eight required-trigger + seven voluntary = 15 deliberations, 74 criterion-3 data points, voluntary:required 12:9 (ratio 1.33). Candidate P4 cases verified in the audit above. Minor correction: S017's file path per the workspace is `provenance/017-oi017-reframing-deliberation/01-deliberation.md`, not `017-oi017-resolution/`; the retrospective should cite the actual path `[workspace-read]`.
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:67:**Q3 (close now vs continue state 3)**. **Close now** at Session 041 close, conditional on the closure-retrospective artefact being produced and passing check 18 + Tier 2 Q8 substantively. The empirical record supports closure: four strong-grade contradiction-prevailing cases, voluntary:required at 1.33, cumulative criterion-3 at 74, §5.3 minority materially activated with no operational blocker. WX-21-2 is discharged by this audit; the contradiction-prevailing data point is not only present but plural.
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:69:**Q4 (§5.2 + §5.3 activation disposition)**. **Vindication on closure.** §5.3 (Outsider "indefinitely movable finish line"): vindicated at 20 successor sessions — exactly the failure mode the Outsider predicted. §5.2 (Articulator close-on-articulation): partially vindicated — the successor-session deferral did produce structural defence value (this retrospective audit is itself that value, and would not have happened at Session 021), but it also accrued the deferral cost the Articulator warned against. If Q3 closes, both minorities move to "vindicated via successor-session retrospective." If Q3 defers, §5.3 strengthens further and §5.2 gains a second activation data point.
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:71:**Q5 (self-application risk)**. The recursion is the **designed structure**, not an accidental gate — Session 041 is the ninth required-trigger deliberation with non-Claude participation, and its evidence contributing to closure is exactly what Closure Procedure §ii requires. Session 021 R4's three grounds hold up: (a) cross-family threshold is met by plural contradiction-prevailing cases; (b) convergence-by-mechanism has survived 20 successor sessions without reopening — vindicated; (c) the asymmetry argument was correct but is now moot. The Skeptic's §6 warning *"the successor audit itself could be conducted without rigour"* `[021/01-deliberation.md §6]` is residual operator-integrity risk; this audit attempts to discharge it substantively.
provenance/041-session-assessment/01C-perspective-retrospective-auditor.md:77:Closure now. Four independently-verified contradiction-prevailing / substantively-augmenting cases (S014, S017, S021, S036) meet the condition-(iii) bar; S021 is load-bearing. The WX-21-2 uncertainty that blocked Session 021 closure is discharged. §5.3 is materially vindicated; continued deferral would itself be the failure mode that minority predicted.
