provenance/044-session-assessment/01-brief-shared.md:183:## 8. Cross-family convergence threshold and minority preservation
provenance/044-session-assessment/01-brief-shared.md:185:Convergence threshold: for substantive moves (MAD v4 spec amendment; new normative clause; engine-v bump), 3-of-4 cross-family convergence suffices IF at least one non-Claude perspective (P3 or P4) is on the prevailing side. If both non-Claude perspectives dissent, the prevailing Claude-only position must be downgraded to non-substantive OR deferred to a future session.
provenance/044-session-assessment/01-brief-shared.md:187:For minor moves (convention adoption with verification window; OI annotation; documentary clarification), 2-of-4 convergence with at least one non-Claude on the prevailing side may suffice at Case Steward discretion.
provenance/044-session-assessment/01-brief-shared.md:189:Minority preservation: any perspective that does not prevail and whose position has distinctive operational content is preserved as a first-class §5-series minority in this session's provenance, with reopen warrants stated. §5.12 (Path-Selection Defender from S043) precedent applies.
provenance/043-session-assessment/01-brief-shared.md:18:The assessment has identified this session as a substantive-revision candidate requiring multi-perspective deliberation per `multi-agent-deliberation.md` v4 §When Multi-Agent Deliberation Is Required, with cross-family participation. Closed-state OI-004 means `d023_4` does not fire; other MAD v4 clauses apply.
